er virtuosere Weise kombiniert werden. Dieser Befund stellt die These vom Aufstieg der Netzwerkgesellschaft in Frage.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aEthnografie. 4aFlughafen. 4aGesellschaft. 4aNetzwerk. 4aOrganisation. 4aOrganisationssoziologie. 4aPanne. 4aSoziologie. 4aTechnik. 4aTechniksoziologie. 4aWartung. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aSociety.  aSociology of Organizations.  aSociology of Technology.  aSociology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Backlist eBook Package 2000-2013z978311102523008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Complete Package 2000-2009z9783110463415oZDB-23-TSO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Sozialw. 2000-2009z9783110463392oZDB-23-TSW0 cprintz978389942649640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839406496?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839406496423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839406496/original  a978-3-11-102523-0  transcript Backlist eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-TSOc2000d2009  aZDB-23-TSWc2000d2009